figurations**\n\nI'm now checking the table configurations to match the specifications. I see the Python backend already queries DynamoDB tables using `db_manager.get_table`, and I see the table names are set by environment or Python config. The instruction is to use `GFF_CLIENTS` and `GFF_PORTAL_ITEMS`. I need to ensure the backend is correctly configured to use these table names for proper DynamoDB integration. This involves verifying and potentially updating the relevant settings.\n\n\n"}}
